S44M1_3_G3A_U01_ALLOCATION_QAFIX_STATUS

sourceId = g3a_u01_3a01
status = WAITING_FOR_LOCAL_TEST

root_cause:
- selected single-KP worksheets used one PatternGroup.
- resolver allocation selected only the first PatternSpec in each PatternGroup.
- multi-spec KPs therefore exposed all PatternSpecs in metadata but generated only the first PatternSpec.
- S44M1-3 digit arrangement regression correctly caught this for max/min/pair coverage.

fixed:
- resolver allocation now expands allocation candidates to each PatternSpec inside each selected PatternGroup.
- question counts are distributed across PatternSpec candidates instead of only PatternGroups.
- this supports digit arrangement max/min/pair and prepares S44M1-4 PatternSpec rotation repair.

local_check:
- git pull public main
- npm test
- git status

next = S44M1-4_G3A_U01_PatternSpecRotationFix after local tests pass
